results.name: Numerators of array which counts positive rational numbers (not including natural numbers).
comment: The sequence of row lengths is [1, 1, 3, 1, 5, 3, 5, 3, 9, 3, 11, 5, 7, 7, ...] = A000010(n)-1 = phi(n)-1, with Euler's totient function phi(n).
For n>=3 delete from the list [seq(j/n-j,j=1..n-2)] the natural numbers and the ratios p/q with (p,q) not 1 (p and q not relatively prime, i.e., p and q have a common divisor >1).
reference: P. Dienes, The Taylor Series, Dover 1957, p. 8, eq.(1).
link: W. Lang, Array of ratios and more.
formula: a(n, k)=numerator(r(n, k)), n>=3, k=1..phi(n)-1, with phi(n):=A000010(n) (Euler's totient function) and the ratios r(n, k) defined for row n above.
xref: Row sums give A111881(n)/A069220(n), n>=3, see the W. Lang link.
Cf. A020652/A020653 if natural numbers are included.
results.author: _Wolfdieter Lang_, Aug 23 2005
